The buzz around James Gunn's next Superman project is undeniable, but many news outlets are missing a crucial detail. While headlines scream "Superman sequel," Gunn himself has a far more expansive vision: the "Superman Saga." Let's set the record straight.

## 窶季unn's Own Words: "Superman Saga" Confirmed

![](https://images.squarespace-cdn.com/content/v1/5d56e145f80b7500016ba502/1430ae71-7812-498d-b873-b9843780f793/james-gunn-shares-superman-bts-photo-with-david-corenswet-v0-fqkza4qm3pbf1.webp)

窶汽uring the Peacemaker Season 2 premiere, DC Studios co-CEO James Gunn made it clear: "I've already finished the treatment for the next story in what I'll call the Superman Saga".He emphasized that this "treatment is done," meaning it is a very worked-out treatment, with production anticipated "not too far away from today".

窶気rucially, Gunn has explicitly stated this project is "not a straight-up Superman sequel". When asked about a "Superman 2" release date on Threads, his response was a telling "Define Superman 2".This highlights that his plans go beyond a simple linear follow-up.

## 窶毅eyond a Sequel: The "Saga" Vision

![](https://images.squarespace-cdn.com/content/v1/5d56e145f80b7500016ba502/6f5f6a73-3eab-4f7f-9795-e14508ad1a8f/GyRY3PFXYAYHkoA.jpg)

窶亀he term "Superman Saga" implies a multi-project narrative arc, far grander than a traditional "sequel." It suggests interconnected stories that could span films, TV series, and appearances in other characters' projects. Warner Bros. Discovery CEO David Zaslav has echoed this, referring to Gunn's upcoming work as "the next installments of the DC Super-Family".

窶亀his broader approach means Superman's story might unfold through team-ups, such as with Supergirl. Her film, Supergirl: Woman of Tomorrow, is set for 2026 and features a cameo in the 2025 Superman movie. Even Peacemaker Season 2 is vital, with Gunn teasing it will "set up all of the rest of the DCU" and feature characters "already met in Superman".

## 窶汽ebunking the Clickbait

窶汽espite Gunn's precise language, headlines like "James Gunn seems to confirm he's working on Superman 2" or "What Is James Gunn Cooking With the Superman Sequel?" have taken over every corner of the interwebs. Gunn directly addressed this, clarifying on Threads: "This is the same movie. Superman has a major role. It's not 'Superman 2.'". These misleading headlines intentionally prioritize clicks over accuracy, distorting the true scope of his plans, and outright confusing normies.

## 窶帰 Core Piece of the New DCU

![](https://images.squarespace-cdn.com/content/v1/5d56e145f80b7500016ba502/0ffdc4f3-dd28-4e8d-baae-4fe53c8d9ad5/Superman_Title_Card.webp)

窶亀he "Superman Saga" is a foundational element of "Gods & Monsters," Chapter One of the rebooted DCU. The 2025 Superman film is the "first major installment," laying the groundwork for a comprehensive "10-year plan". With the next story's treatment complete, a 2026 filming timeline could see the next "Superman Saga" film released around 2027.

窶偽nderstanding this nuanced "Saga" vision is key to appreciating the future of the DCU. It is not just about one more film; it is about building a cohesive, interconnected universe for the Man of Steel and the entire Super-Family.